Apple, famously, figured out the right interface for the smartphone, and bu=
ilt an entirely new operating system around touch. Yes, iOS is based on mac=
OS at a low level, but it was a completely new operating system in a way th=
at Windows Mobile was not; at the same time, because iOS was based on macOS=
, it was far more capable than smartphone-only alternatives like BlackBerry=
 OS or PalmOS. The key aspect of this capability was that the iPhone could =
access the real Internet.

What is funny is that Steve Jobs=E2=80=99 initial announcement of this capa=
bility was met with much less enthusiasm than the iPhone=E2=80=99s other tw=
o selling points of being a widescreen iPod and a mobile phone:

( https://videopress.com/embed/3OlG8bv1?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
